You have an existing render props pattern component (DataFetcher) that needs migration to a custom hook. Requirements:

**Original Render Props Implementation:**
tsx
<DataFetcher url="/api/users">
  {(data, loading, error, refetch) => (
    <div>
      {loading && <p>Loading...</p>}
      {error && <p>Error: {error}</p>}
      {data && <UserList users={data} />}
      <button onClick={refetch}>Refresh</button>
    </div>
  )}
</DataFetcher>


**Requirements for Hook Version:**
1. Create `useFetch` hook that maintains same API
2. **Prevent unnecessary re-renders** - Child components shouldn't re-render on every state update
3. **Memoize returned values** - Use useMemo to prevent reference changes
4. **Handle abort on unmount** - Cancel in-flight requests when component unmounts
5. **Error boundaries support** - Propagate errors properly
6. **Parallel requests** - Support multiple concurrent fetches
7. **Cache management** - Optional caching layer to prevent duplicate requests

**Example Hook Usage:**
tsx
function UserListPage() {
  const { data, loading, error, refetch } = useFetch('/api/users');

  return (
    <div>
      {loading && <p>Loading...</p>}
      {error && <p>Error: {error}</p>}
      {data && <UserList users={data} />}
      <button onClick={refetch}>Refresh</button>
    </div>
  );
}


**Edge cases:**
- Rapid remount/unmount cycles
- URL/options changes during fetch
- Race conditions with multiple fetches
- Memory leaks from AbortController
- Stale closure issues

